coupled_prompt_600:
Renault Twingo II – The Original

The Renault Twingo II is a very old motorway linking France and Belgium on the A1 motorway from Paris to Antwerp. It had its heyday in 2000 when Renault sold it at an auction for €4.2 million (approximately £3.9 million today).

As you will see, it has been around a long time but never made much noise in terms of performance. So it makes sense that it remains in service well into our time.

The Twingo was a predecessor to the Renault Zoe which was launched in 2008. The Zoe would be replaced by the Zoe Q5 in 2016 with the Zoe Q7 coming later in 2017.
